<p dir="auto" class="break-words" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Even just the first half‚ÄĒDavid vanishing, meeting the ship, starting his journey‚ÄĒcarries a quiet lift. For a five-year-old, it‚Äôs a kid facing the unknown, and that‚Äôs huge. The commercials probably showed him scared but brave, and the box art (that sleek ship!) promised something amazing ahead. Your idea of him projecting his thoughts forward adds a spiritual kick: he‚Äôs not just lost, he‚Äôs <em>aiming</em> for something, like a little prayer in motion. Not seeing the end might‚Äôve made it more uplifting‚ÄĒhis fate stayed a hopeful ‚Äúhe‚Äôs gonna make it,‚ÄĚ a blank slate of faith.</p>
