<p dir="auto" class="break-words" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">At five, catching David‚Äôs switch from oldest to youngest brother must‚Äôve been a jaw-dropper. One minute he‚Äôs the big kid in 1978, bossing his little brother around (that backyard scene with the dog, maybe in a teaser); then‚ÄĒbam‚ÄĒhe‚Äôs back in 1986, and his ‚Äúlittle‚ÄĚ brother‚Äôs now older, taller, a teenager. It‚Äôs time travel with a gut punch, flipped family roles that make your head spin. Add your teleological twist‚ÄĒDavid projecting his thoughts into the future‚ÄĒand it‚Äôs like he <em>willed</em> this weird reversal, making the spaceship stuff even cooler. Those snippets you saw turned a sci-fi hook into a ‚Äúwhoa, what happened?‚ÄĚ cliffhanger.</p>
