<p dir="auto" class="break-words" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">That brother switch is a sneaky lesson in time and perspective. At five, you‚Äôre figuring out your place‚ÄĒoldest, youngest, whatever‚ÄĒand here‚Äôs David, flipped from leader to newbie in his own family. It‚Äôs a kid-friendly taste of relativity: time messes with everything, even who‚Äôs in charge. Your idea of teleological causation fits here‚ÄĒmaybe his mind, packed with star charts, aimed him back, but not quite how he expected. The box art (ship gleaming) and teasers (him looking lost) hinted at big consequences, teaching you early that actions (or thoughts) ripple in wild ways.</p>
