<p dir="auto" class="break-words" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Fred getting shut out by that college jerk bothered you because it‚Äôs the opposite of uplifting‚ÄĒyet the movie‚Äôs spirit sneaks in anyway. His neotenous core‚ÄĒwanting to play, to share, despite rejection‚ÄĒholds a quiet glow. At 11, that might‚Äôve frustrated you, but it‚Äôs also hopeful: Fred keeps being Fred, not hardening up. Your teleological spin fits‚ÄĒhe‚Äôs aiming for connection, not just success, and even if he doesn‚Äôt get it there, he keeps going (like finding a friend later). It‚Äôs uplifting not in a loud win, but in that stubborn, youthful faith you felt he deserved. Dede‚Äôs role, too‚ÄĒless vicarious, more protective‚ÄĒadds a tender lift you sensed beyond the clich√©.</p>
