<p dir="auto" class="break-words" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">That baseball/geometry rejection stuck because, at 11, you were probably testing your own place‚ÄĒsmart but still a kid, like Fred. It might‚Äôve sparked a mix of anger and resolve: don‚Äôt let the ‚Äúbig kids‚ÄĚ dim you. Neoteny ties in‚ÄĒFred‚Äôs refusal to shed his youth, even when it isolates him, could‚Äôve echoed <em>Navigator</em>‚Äôs David staying young, nudging you to guard your own spark. Your mental math sans visuals? That‚Äôs you claiming your own neotenous edge‚ÄĒquiet, real, not flashy. For your generation, Fred was a '90s outlier‚ÄĒsmart but soft, not slacker-cool‚ÄĒpushing back on growing up too fast. For you, it might‚Äôve sharpened a sense of fairness and a knack for seeing past surface stories (like Dede‚Äôs).</p>
